'''Line 2''' of the [[Changsha Metro]] ({{zh|s=长沙地铁二号线|p=Chǎngshā Dìtiě Èr Hào Xiàn}}) is a [[rapid transit]] line running from west to east [[Changsha]] crossing the [[Xiang River]]. The Phase 1 of the line was opened on 29 April 2014 with 19 stations, and the western extension opened on 28 December 2015 with 4 stations.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.hunan.gov.cn/zw/hnyw/szdt/201512/t20151229_2836589.html|title=长沙地铁2号线西延一期载客试运营|author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=28 December 2015 |website=Government of Hunan|publisher= |accessdate=30 December 2015 }}</ref> This line is 26.57&nbsp;km long with 23 stations.<ref name="railwaygazette2014">{{cite web|url=http://www.railwaygazette.com/news/urban/single-view/view/changsha-metro-opens.html|title=Changsha metro opens |author=<!--Staff writer(s); no by-line.--> |date=29 April 2014 |website=Railway Gazette |publisher= |accessdate=4 May 2014}}</ref>

